      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Tricky race with little between the top half dozen. BUSH ETIQUETTE (3) is a former Victorian who ran well below expectations first try in this area. That was a hot form race and immediately spelled again so there may have been excuses. Trip suits fresh and best figures more than stack up so worth another try. SMALL TOWN HUSSLER (1) is fitter for two runs back and looks close to a win. First try at the trip but will go forward and take catching. KAJETAN (4) has wound up well the last couple, the latest a near miss here over 1200m. Will be winding up late. WE US 'N' CO (6) was safely held fresh over the shorter dash then got home late last time here when seventh in the same race as KAJETAN, but beaten only a length. Among the main hopes again. TORANAGA (2) turned in a good run first try in this area and among the better chances in this lineup.",
